Online Course Marketplace









Objectives
 
•  Develop a marketplace where instructors can publish courses and learners can enroll and study.
•  Support video lectures, quizzes, assignments, and progress tracking.
•  Create a scalable platform that incentivizes both learning and content creation.
 
Deliverables
•  A fully functional Online Course Marketplace.
•  Instructor dashboard for course creation and student management.
•  Learner dashboard with enrolled courses and progress tracking.
•  Video player with chapter navigation and notes.
•  Certificate generation upon course completion.
 
Requirements
•  HTML: Structure course pages, video player, and dashboards.
•  CSS: Design a professional and distraction-free learning interface.
•  JavaScript: Handle video playback, quiz interactivity, and progress updates.
•  Backend: Manage enrollments, payments, and course content delivery.
•  Database: Store courses, users, enrollments, and quiz results.
 
Advanced Features
•  Q&A; Section: Allow learners to ask questions on each lecture.
•  Discussion Forums: Course-specific forums for peer interaction.
•  Instructor Earnings: Revenue sharing dashboard for instructors.
•  Course Bundles: Group related courses at a discounted price.
•  Live Classes: Integrate video conferencing for live sessions.
•  Adaptive Learning: Suggest next steps based on quiz performance.
•  Multilingual Support: Offer courses and subtitles in multiple languages.
•  Offline Access: Allow downloaded lessons for offline viewing.
•  Mobile Responsiveness: Smooth learning experience on all devices.
•  Admin Analytics: Enrollment trends, top courses, and revenue reports.
•  Payment Gateway: Handle course purchases and subscriptions securely via Stripe with receipt emails.
•  Instructor Payouts: Automatically distribute monthly revenue shares to instructors via Stripe Connect.
•  Refund Portal: Allow students to self-service request refunds within a configurable policy window.
